The paper proposes a technique to improve the training and testing efficiency of linear SVM for large-scale machine learning problems, which is a common topic in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed technique involves minwise hashing, which is a popular method in information retrieval (cs.IR) and data mining (cs.DS) for similarity search and dimensionality reduction. The paper also discusses the positive definiteness of matrices, which is a fundamental concept in linear algebra and optimization, and has applications in various subfields of computer science such as databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
